      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think somewhere we need to clearly document what a commit index means.  Does each branch start at index 0?  Intuitively, a commit with no parents should have an index of zero, but what happens during a merge?  Does the next commit get the highest index of any of its parents, plus one?  How often are the indexes recomputed?  What happens if history is changed?",
